Description

Rovinj has always been a favourite destination of curious travellers and artists. Let this boutique hotel take you through the art history of Rovinj through its impressive collection of artworks, its terrace with an atmosphere of a living room in the middle of the town, local food inspired by the centuries-old hotel tradition, and a bar with the widest selection of whiskey in Croatia. There are only 14 rooms and 4 suites in the Adriatic Hotel.

The Sessa C42 reveals its dual nature in its ample, comfortable spaces, inherent in its great dynamic style. The innovative design of the cockpit, with its semi-circular table and sofas, the large sunbathing areas on the stern and bow, and the spacious indoor areas, all serve as an invitation to set sail. Without stopovers, without limits, maybe even without a goal in mind. If not that of enjoying the sea down to the last wave. This motor yacht is a synonym for elegance and a sporty personality.

Specifications: Engine: max hp 620/ Kw 456, fuel capacity: 2x345 l, fresh water capacity: 250 l, tender dimension: 1,60 m x 1,30 m, overall length: 13,12m, beam: 3.85m
Inclusions: fuel, docking fees, breakfast, crew, accommodation on a yacht
Exclusions: food (dinners and lunches)

Sessa C42 has great outdoor areas, convivial cockpit characterized by a spacious ‘‘L’’ shape sofa that turns into a sunbathing area, friendly use and solid electric bimini top to increase protection at aft, together with her wide sun pad at bow, charming salon in the main deck with their private view of the sea guaranteed by her huge panoramic windows, spacious galley, 2 cabins with direct access to their private and roomy heads with separated showers and much more.

Excursion

Private excursion to Konavle region including wine tasting, lunch and visit to Sokol Fortress
(approx. 7 hours)

Konavle Countryside Experience

Meeting point: hotel lobby @ 10:00
Duration: approx. 7 hours

Combination of sightseeing, wine tasting and good food, this tour is made to satisfy all your senses! Your private tour will take you along the coast above Dubrovnik town with a stop on Orsula. This position has the best panoramic viewpoint to the Old town, ideal for taking photos of Dubrovnik. You will continue further down to the region of Cavtat, a small township in Dubrovnik region. Upon arrival in Cavtat this tour will take you along the city where you will visit the famous Mausoleum of Cavtat´s native family Racic.

Inclusions: private guide, round transfers, tickets for Mausoleum of Cavtat´s native family Racic and Sokol fortress, wine tasting and lunch
Exclusions: gratuities and items purchased for personal use


After this point you will continue by car further to the Winery Crvik which is situated in Konavle, a 10 km south from the city of Cavtat. There you will taste local wine and snacks at wine producers’ family cellar. After wine tasting tour continues up to the hills where fortress Sokol is situated. After the sightseeing of the fortress, you will continue to the next destination, one of the finest agritourism’s in Cilipi where you will have traditional lunch and tour of the estate.


Notes: Please let us know: if you have any food dislikes or allergies

Wednesday @ 09:00

Excursion

Private excursion to Hum and Motovun including brandy tasting and lunch with drinks
(8 hours)

Medieval gems and gourmet of Northern Istria

Meeting point: hotel lobby @ 09:00
Duration: 8 hours

Today you will enjoy a full day tour of northern part of Istria – picturesque towns Hum, Motovun and Istria’s countryside. Get to know history and tradition with your personal guide - sightseeing, brandy tasting, and traditional cuisine is on the menu! The tour with start with a transfer to Hum, officially the smallest town in the world. After the brandy tasting, next stop will be Motovun – unique hilltop town known among other things for a film festival. Your tour will continue to great truffle restourant where you will have lunch.


Notes: Fun facts: According to the legend, Hum arose when the Giants built towns in the valley of the river Mirna and with the remaining stones, they built Hum.
Inclusions: private guide, tickets, round transfers, brandy tasting at Aura and lunch
Exclusions: gratuities and items purchased for personal use

Day on your leisure

Day on your leisure

We suggest you to visit town of Fazana where you can embark on a boat that will take you to the National Park Brijuni. N.P. Brijuni consists of 14 islands that are situated on a 7-km stretch between Pula and Rovinj. Nature has created quite a little paradise here – a true harmony of flora and fauna, historical monuments and comfortable hotels. Brijuni, a group of islands comprising of two large and twelve smaller isles, are strung along Istria’s south western coast not far from Pula. Brijuni are renowned for its nature and the unspoiled Mediterranean vegetation, but the islands also boast an invaluable cultural heritage dating from the Roman and Byzantine times.


Notes: if desired private guide can be arranged, just advise us!
Exclusions: transfers, food, drinks, tour, private guide and tickets
